# Git workflow

## Branching

- **Never** commit or push directly to `develop` or `main` unless the user explicitly asks.
- For new work, branch off `develop`:
  - `feature/<short-description>`
  - `fix/<short-description>`
  - `chore/<short-description>`

## Commits and pushes

1. Commit only on the feature branch.
2. Push the feature branch to `origin`.
3. Open a **draft PR** with base branch **`develop`**.
4. Do not merge unless the user asks.

## Pull requests

- Default merge target: **`develop`** (not `main`).
- PR titles: prefix with `[Cursor] ` when the agent authors the change.
- Include a short summary and test plan in the PR body.

## Promoting to main

- PRs to `main` are for release/integration of `develop`, not for routine feature work.

## Example

```bash
git checkout develop
git pull origin develop
git checkout -b feature/session-persistence
# ... make changes, commit ...
git push -u origin feature/session-persistence
gh pr create --draft --base develop --head feature/session-persistence
```
